phase2.explanation:
pop() throws EmptyStackException when called on an empty stack!

FIX: Check if empty first:
if (!stack.isEmpty()) {
    System.out.println(stack.pop());
} else {
    System.out.println("Stack is empty!");
}

Or use peek() which also throws EmptyStackException.

Similarly, for Queue:
• poll() returns null if empty (safe)
• remove() throws NoSuchElementException (unsafe)

Always prefer the safe versions:
• poll() over remove()
• peek() over element()
• offer() over add()

